      "writtenOn": "2020-10-20T22:28:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This means that this thread will be blocked for as long as it takes to get to the next event.\nIf the session file is corrupted or if something went wrong during the recording, this could block this thread for a long time and \"StopReplay()\" wouldn\u0027t work.\n\nIs that correct?\nShouldn\u0027t we unblock periodically to check if a REPLAY_STOP message is available?",
